@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Font Family";
    ViewData["DemoNumber"] = 12;
}
<div class="mx-auto max-w-screen-2xl px-4 py-6 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[260px_1fr]">
        <partial name="Demos/_DemoLayout" />
        <div>
            <div class="demo-card">
                <div class="demo-card-header">Font Family</div>
                <div class="demo-card-body">
                    <p class="demo-description">Change the typeface of selected text using the font name dropdown in the toolbar. The editor includes a variety of web-safe and system fonts suitable for documents, emails, and web content.</p>

                    <richtextbox
                        id="fontFamilyEditor"
                        name="fontFamilyEditor"
                        toolbar="default"
                        width="100%"
                        height="300px"
                        html="<h2>Typography Style Guide</h2><p>Choosing the right font family sets the tone for your document. Here are common choices grouped by category:</p><h3>Serif Fonts</h3><p><span style='font-family:Georgia'>Georgia works well for long-form articles and editorial content. Its generous letter spacing improves readability on screens.</span></p><p><span style='font-family:Times New Roman'>Times New Roman remains a standard choice for academic papers, legal documents, and formal correspondence.</span></p><h3>Sans-Serif Fonts</h3><p><span style='font-family:Arial'>Arial is a versatile sans-serif font used widely in business documents and presentations.</span></p><p><span style='font-family:Verdana'>Verdana was designed specifically for on-screen readability, making it a strong pick for web interfaces.</span></p><h3>Monospace Fonts</h3><p><span style='font-family:Courier New'>Courier New is the go-to monospace font for displaying code snippets, terminal output, and tabular data where character alignment matters.</span></p>"></richtextbox>

                    <div class="demo-note">
                        <div class="demo-note-content">
                            <div class="demo-note-title">Note</div>
                            <p class="demo-note-text">The font family dropdown includes web-safe fonts. Custom fonts can be added via content CSS.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="code-panel">
                        <pre><code>&lt;richtextbox
    name="fontFamilyEditor"
    toolbar="default"
    height="300px" /&gt;</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
